jobs_results.title: Senior Software Engineer
jobs_results.description:
Ninja Van is a late-stage logtech startup that is disrupting a massive industry with innovation and cutting edge technology. Launched 2014 in Singapore, we have grown rapidly to become one of Southeast Asia's largest and fastest-growing express logistics companies. Since our inception, we’ve delivered to 100 million different customers across the region with added predictability, flexibility and convenience. Join us in our mission to connect shippers and shoppers across Southeast Asia to a world of new possibilities.

More about us:
• We process 250 million API requests and 3TB of data every day.
• We deliver more than 1.5 million parcels every day.
• 100% network coverage with 1000+ hubs and stations in 6 SEA markets (Singapore, Malaysia, Indonesia, Thailand, Vietnam and Philippines), reaching 500 million consumers.
• 600,000 active shippers in all e-commerce segments, from the largest marketplaces to the individual social commerce sellers.
• Raised US$400 million over four... rounds.

We are looking for world-class talent to join our crack team of engineers, product managers and designers. We want people who are passionate about creating software that makes a difference to the world. We like people who are brimming with ideas and who take initiative rather than wait to be told what to do. We prize team-first mentality, personal responsibility and tenacity to solve hard problems and meet deadlines. As part of a small and lean team, you will have a very direct impact on the success of the company.

Role & Responsibilities
• Design, develop and maintain software that powers Ninja Van's complex logistics operations.
• Help design the architecture, own development of major initiatives and modules.
• Work in cross functional teams with product managers, UX designers and QA engineers to ship software on-quality and on-time.
• Help level up the team; share knowledge, conduct code and design review; drive code quality and process improvement initiatives.
• Write code that you are proud of, with extensibility, scalability and performance in mind.

Requirements
• Solid Computer Science fundamentals, excellent problem-solving skills.
• 3-6 years of backend or frontend development in a product company, with a proven track record of shipping successful software products.
• Deep experience in most of our tech stack or similar technologies.
• Bachelor’s or Master’s degree in Computer Science or related field from a top university.

Tech stack:
• Data storage: MySQL, TiDB, Elasticsearch
• Cache: Hazelcast, Redis
• Real-time data pipeline: Apache Kafka
• Backend: Play (Java 8), GoLang, Node.js
• Frontend: React, AngularJS
• Mobile: Android SDK, Dart (Flutter), React Native
• Orchestrator: Kubernetes
• Containerization: Docker, Containerd
• Cloud Provider: GCP, AWS
• Architecture: Micro Services (Frontend and Backend)

Submit a job application

By applying to the job, you acknowledge that you have read, understood and agreed to our Privacy Policy Notice (the “Notice”) and consent to the collection, use and/or disclosure of your personal data by Ninja Logistics Pte Ltd (the “Company”) for the purposes set out in the Notice. In the event that your job application or personal data was received from any third party pursuant to the purposes set out in the Notice, you warrant that such third party has been duly authorised by you to disclose your personal data to us for the purposes set out in the the Notice.

Ninja Van focuses on Enterprise Software, E-Commerce, Transportation, Logistics, and Content Delivery. Their company has offices in Singapore and Special Capital Region of Jakarta. They have a large team that's between 501-1000 employees. To date, Ninja Van has raised $32.5M of funding; their latest round was closed on April 2016.

You can view their website at https://www.ninjavan.co/ or find them on Twitter, Facebook, and LinkedIn

jobs_results.title: Senior Software Quality Assurance Engineer
jobs_results.description:
We are currently looking for a Senior Software Quality Assurance engineer to work on our quality management systems. You will be working on establishing and executing software quality assurance processes and procedures. From the control plans, to audits and facilitating corrective actions teams; the whole Software Quality Assurance is your arena.

Things You'll Get To Work On
• Establishing and executing software quality assurance processes
• Oversees Internal Software Quality Assurance, providing direction, advice, and guidance
• Develops control plan with new and existing product/service lines
• Conducts system, process and software quality audits
• Facilitates corrective action teams
• Performs root cause analysis and verification of corrective actions of conditions adverse to quality

Education And Experience We Want From You
• MS or BS in computer science, computer engineering or related field
• 5+ years professional work experience as a software quality assurance... engineer

Skills And Traits You Will Likely Already Have
• Excellent knowledge of international quality standards such as IATF 16949 and ISO 9001 (ISO preferred, but IATF would be nice to have)
• Strong experience with Software Development Life Cycle, comfortable with both waterfall and Agile methodologies in a V-Model systems development environment
• Strong experience with software improvement model/s e.g. ASPICE, CMMI
• Familiar with Software Quality Control tools (e.g., Klokwork, HelixQAC, cppcheck, shellcheck, OR Tools C++)
• Familiar with software testing tools for unit test, verification testing (e.g., AI, dSPACE, Simphera)
• Familiar with relational database management system (PLM, DCRM)
• Experienced in Quality Management system auditing
• Technical editorial skills
• Good interpersonal skills

Bonus Points (but Not Required)
• C++ Experience or any coding experience
• Experience with creating and executing software test plan
• Certified Auditor
• Experience with ISO 2626

Motional is making driverless vehicles a safe, reliable, and accessible reality.
Our team is commercializing a world-class driverless system. The Motional team is behind some of the industry’s largest leaps forward in the last decade, including the first fully-autonomous cross-country drive in the U.S, the launch of the world’s first robotaxi pilot, and operation of the world’s most-established public robotaxi fleet. Strategically formed by Hyundai Motor Group and Aptiv, Motional is fundamentally changing how people move through their lives.

Headquartered in Boston, Motional has operations in the US and Asia. For more information, visit www.Motional.com and follow us on Twitter, LinkedIn, Facebook, Instagram and YouTube.

Motional AD Inc. is an EOE. We celebrate diversity and are committed to creating an inclusive environment for all employees. To comply with Federal Law, we participate in E-Verify. All newly-hired employees are queried through this electronic system established by the DHS and the SSA to verify their identity and employment eligibility

jobs_results.title: Senior Software Engineer, Cloud Threat Detection Product
jobs_results.description:
At Horangi we’re building Warden, a multi-cloud solution that enables continuous cloud security, compliance monitoring and risk management for AWS and GCP. Warden deploys in minutes, delivering actionable insights to help our customers identify, prioritize and fix security threats in their multi-cloud environments.

Horangi is looking for experienced senior software engineers to join our team. You will be part of an engineering team building scalable systems capable of detecting real time threats and adversarial activities within our customer’s cloud environment.

Your team will build a rule-based and behavior-based analysis engine that monitors real-time events and log streams from multiple cloud providers to identify real threats faster, thereby reducing time to remediation. You will plan detection based on real-world data and well-understood scenarios, and codify threat detection rules that can be rapidly deployed.
What you’ll be doing
• You will design and develop stream... processing infrastructure and application
• You will build a scalable system that can handle events at scale
• You will work with AWS technologies like Amazon Kinesis, DynamoDB and EventBridge
• You will help build a framework for our threat detection engine and a repeatable process of building rules
• You will learn to encode security insights into automation
• You will continuously monitor system health and optimize performance
What we’re looking for
• You have at least 5 years experience in backend engineering. Python is your lingua franca
• You are experienced with designing and building products with AWS and serverless technologies
• You are a strong communicator. Explaining complex technical concepts to non-technical audiences is not a problem for you
• You possess strong computer science fundamentals: data structures distributed systems, networking and graph algorithms
• You write high quality code, that can be safely co-authored in a fast grown organization
• You have a good understanding of how various cloud services work across all major cloud providers. Relevant cloud certification is a strong bonus
• You have a bachelor’s degree in Computer Science, Engineering or related field, or equivalent training, fellowship, or work experience
Bonus points if you have
• You have experience building real-time stream processing systems
• You have prior experience in cybersecurity or intelligence fields
• You have knowledge of CI/CD & DevOps tools
• Contributed to open source projects

At Horangi, we pride ourselves as Cloud Security Champions in Asia backed by a team of global cybersecurity experts and trusted by Industry Leaders such as Gojek, MoneySmart, PropertyGuru and Tiket.com.

We built our Cloud Security product using AWS technology and cloud best practices to provide the security, performance and reliability of our platform as we ship rapidly in our agile software development. We adopt an event-driven architecture and embrace serverless technologies that are backed with 100% infrastructure as code. We build our app using reliable tools and frameworks that our team knows and trusts, including Python, Docker, TypeScript, React and GraphQL.

Horangi has a positive, diverse, and supportive culture, and we look for people who are curious, inventive, and work to be a little better every single day. We work in a fast-paced, dynamic and get-things-done culture. Horangi is always looking to hire collaborative, humble and highly driven individuals who want to make a difference.

Level yourself up as a cloud security expert and do the best work of your life here at Horangi
